Firſt then, hear Dr. Robert Barnes, viz. The whole Church prayeth, LORD forgive us our Sins;
                  See his works, p. 254. 
                  wherefore ſhe hath ſpots and wrincles: But by acknowledging them (through the Merits of Chriſt) her wrincles be ſcratched out, &c.

Iſidorus ſaith. The Leſſon (in the Church) bringeth great profit to the Hearers;

   Iſidor. de Eccleſ. offic. l. 1 c. 10. 
Therefore when ſinging is, let all ſing together, when prayer is, let all pray together; and when the Leſſon or Chapter is read, let ſilence be made, and let all hear together.
